1. Introduction
The container liner shipping industry is a dynamic and complex one. It consists of a fleet of vessels with a common ownership or management strategy, providing a fixed service at regular intervals between ports of call and offers transport of containerized goods in the catchment area

served by those ports of call (Stopford, 2009). At present, a large proportion (i.e. 80%) of world commodities by volume is transported by seaborne trade and more than 62% of this seaborne trade is carried by the CLSI (UNCTAD, 2012; Mohd Salleh et al., 2014). A recent study

http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.ajsl.2017.06.007
2092-5212/© 2017 The Korean Association of Shipping and Logistics, Inc. Production and hosting by Elsevier B.V. Peer review under responsibility of the Korean Association of Shipping and Logistics, Inc.

