5. Results and Discussion
Within this paper, a model for analyzing the arrival punctuality of a vessel by using an FRBBN model is developed. In this model, the arrival punctuality depends upon many criteria, which are port conditions, vessel conditions, process management efficiency by agency and departure punctuality from the previous port of call. It is noteworthy to mention that this developed model is highly sensitive. Any alteration of criteria values will also alter the arrival punctuality’s value. In test case 1, based on the given datasets in Table 8, the arrival punctuality value of ܸ݁‫݈݁ݏݏ‬஺ at ܲ‫ݐݎ݋‬஺ is evaluated as 92.1%. This arrival punctuality value is not fixed and will change if a criterion’s value is altered. To justify these statements, the deviation of arrival punctuality of ܸ݁‫݈݁ݏݏ‬஺ at ܲ‫ݐݎ݋‬஺ due to alteration of each criterion as shown in Table 11 is evaluated.

Table 11 Arrival punctuality’s value at different environments
Description of Event (Change of Event) Departure from previous port is 100% serious delay Weather condition at port is 100% rough Punctuality of pilotage operation is 100% serious delay Tidal window is 100% restrictive Berthing area condition is 100% densely congested Port yard condition is 100% densely congested Port administration process is 100% low efficiency Inland corridor is 100% densely congested En-route traffic condition is 100% dense traffic Missing a convoy at a canal occurs En-route weather condition is 100% rough Machinery breakdown is 100% major Ship’s staff are 100% low reliability Dangerous event occurs Other unexpected delays occur Country reliability is 100% low reliability Agency is 100% low reliability

